: [778.1, 153.8, 842.5, 172.2]}, {"text": "Subsidiary", "bbox": [772.8, 175.1, 848.1, 193.5]}, {"text": "Standard Market Property", "bbox": [347.5, 132.7, 524.8, 151.1]}, {"text": "Casualty Insurance", "bbox": [370.9, 153.8, 501.4, 172.2]}, {"text": "Subsidiaries", "bbox": [393.5, 175.1, 474.9, 193.5]}, {"text": "Life Insurance", "bbox": [575.5, 153.8, 671.6, 172.2]}, {"text": "Subsidiary", "bbox": [586.1, 175.1, 661.6, 193.5]}, {"text": "As of February 26, 2010, our credit and financial strength ratings were:", "bbox": [127.5, 58.0, 765.5, 81.7]}, {"text": "On August 6, 2009, Fitch Ratings lowered our ratings and changed the rating outlook to stable. Our parent", "bbox": [127.5, 408.5, 1077.6, 432.1]}, {"text": "company senior debt rating was lowered from A- to BBB+ and our standard market property casualty", "bbox": [127.5, 432.1, 1029.1, 455.8]}, {"text": "subsidiaries’ insurance and life insurance subsidiary financial strength ratings were lowered from AA- to A+.", "bbox": [127.5, 455.8, 1089.7, 479.4]}, {"text": "Fitch said the rating action was primarily driven by our unfavorable property casualty underwriting", "bbox": [127.5, 479.4, 1001.6, 503.0]}, {"text": "performance during 2008 and the first half of 2009. Fitch said it viewed favorably our steps taken with our", "bbox": [127.5, 503.0, 1080.9, 526.7]}, {"text": "investment portfolio. Fitch also noted our strong capitalization and low operating leverage. No other ratings", "bbox": [127.5, 526.7, 1085.1, 550.3]}, {"text": "agency actions occurred during 2009.", "bbox": [127.5, 550.3, 469.6, 573.9]}, {"text": "On February 18, 2010, A.M. Best affirmed our ratings that it had assigned in December 2008, continuing its", "bbox": [127.5, 580.2, 1092.6, 603.8]}, {"text": "stable outlook. A.M. Best cited our superior risk-adjusted capitalization, strong five-year average operating", "bbox": [127.5, 603.8, 1074.1, 627.4]}, {"text": "performance, historically redundant reserves and successful distribution within our targeted regional", "bbox": [127.5, 627.4, 1026.3, 651.1]}, {"text": "markets. A.M. Best noted that common stock leverage was approximately 50 percent of statutory surplus", "bbox": [127.5, 651.0, 1070.7, 674.7]}, {"text": "at year-end 2009, a concern offset by our conservative underwriting and reserving philosophies, with loss", "bbox": [127.5, 674.7, 1066.2, 698.3]}, {"text": "reserves more than fully covered by a highly rated, diversified bond portfolio.", "bbox": [127.5, 698.3, 812.4, 722.0]}, {"text": "Our debt ratings are discussed in Item 7, Liquidity and Capital Resources, Additional Sources of Liquidity,", "bbox": [127.5, 728.2, 1065.2, 751.8]}, {"text": "Page 69.", "bbox": [127.5, 751.8, 213.0, 775.5]}, {"text": "Operating Structure", "bbox": [127.5, 781.4, 344.2, 809.7]}, {"text": "We offer our broad array of insurance products through the independent agency channel. We recognize that", "bbox": [127.5, 816.1, 1090.9, 839.8]}, {"text": "locally based independent agencies have relationships in their communities and local marketplace", "bbox": [127.5, 839.8, 1013.4, 863.4]}, {"text": "intelligence that can lead to policyholder satisfaction, loyalty and profitable business. We seek to be a", "bbox": [127.5, 863.4, 1038.3, 887.0]}, {"text": "consistent and predictable property casualty carrier that agencies can rely on to serve their clients. For our", "bbox": [127.5, 887.0, 1076.7, 910.7]}, {"text": "standard market business, field and headquarters underwriters make risk-specific decisions about both", "bbox": [127.5, 910.7, 1053.6, 934.3]}, {"text": "new business and renewals.", "bbox": [127.5, 934.3, 387.5, 957.9]}, {"text": "In our 10 highest volume states for consolidated property casualty premiums, 933 reporting agency", "bbox": [127.5, 964.2, 1020.1, 987.8]}, {"text": "locations wrote 68.1 percent of our 2009 consolidated property casualty earned premium volume", "bbox": [127.5, 987.8, 1003.0, 1011.4]}, {"text": "compared with 910 locations and 68.7 percent in 2008.", "bbox": [127.5, 1011.4, 632.9, 1035.1]}]}